SEQUENCE:8
DESCRIPTION;LANGUAGE=en-US:Dear all\,\n\nThis is an invitation for the CPDS
 E episode meeting on 30 June 2026 a part of the episode meetings series.\n
 \nWe will have these meetings every six weeks as a physical meeting altern
 ating between SDU and KU. The meetings at KU will be at CPDSE\, Jagtvej 16
 0\, 1st floor and at SDU you can use this map<https://clients.mapsindoors.
 com/sdu/573f26e4bc1f571b08094312/search> to guide you to the meeting room.
 \n\nOur default agenda is:\n\n  *   Circle Sync: Individual circles meet i
 nternally to review their progress on the Episode's goal. The output is a 
 clear status update to share with the larger group. Commitments are captur
 ed directly as Todo-items and decisions are documented as Messages.\n  *  
  Break / Lunch 🥪\n  *   Center Sync: All circles come together to share
  their progress. Each circle presents a brief\, high-level summary of thei
 r work\, highlighting key accomplishments and any dependencies or blockers
 .\n  *   Pharma Data Science Showcase: Research Circle organizes scientifi
 c talks and workshops (Storebælt series).\n\nWe will be serving lunch at 
 the meeting\, so we kindly ask that you reply to the invitation\, so we kn
 ow how many people to expect. If you have any dietary restrictions/allergi
 es\, please let Jeppe know.\n\nLooking forward to seeing you.\n\nBest\,\nM
 orten & Jeppe\n\nJeppe Hartmann\nProject Coordinator\n\nUniversity of Cope
 nhagen\nDepartment of Drug Design and Pharmacology\n\nUniversitetsparken 2
 \nDK - 2100 Copenhagen\nDenmark\nLync/Skype +45 35323413\njeppe.hartmann@s
 und.ku.dk<mailto:jeppe.hartmann@sund.ku.dk>\n\n[Logo for Københavns Unive
 rsitet]\n\nHow we protect personal data<https://informationssikkerhed.ku.d
 k/english/protection-of-information-privacy/privacy-policy/>\n\n\n
