SEQUENCE:9
DESCRIPTION;LANGUAGE=en-US:Dear all\,\n\nWe have the pleasure of inviting y
 ou to our CPDSE Episode Meetings.\n\nWe will have these meetings every six
  weeks as a physical meeting alternating between SDU and KU. The meetings 
 at KU will be at CPDSE\, Jagtvej 160\, 1st floor and at SDU you can use th
 is map<https://clients.mapsindoors.com/sdu/573f26e4bc1f571b08094312/search
 > to guide you to the meeting room. The meetings are usually on a Tuesday\
 , but for this specific meeting we will have it on a Wednesday.\n\nOur def
 ault agenda is:\n\n  *   Circle Sync: Individual circles meet internally t
 o review their progress on the Episode's goal. The output is a clear statu
 s update to share with the larger group. Commitments are captured directly
  as Todo-items and decisions are documented as Messages.\n  *   Break / Lu
 nch 🥪\n  *   Center Sync: All circles come together to share their prog
 ress. Each circle presents a brief\, high-level summary of their work\, hi
 ghlighting key accomplishments and any dependencies or blockers.\n  *   Ph
 arma Data Science Showcase: Research Circle organizes scientific talks and
  workshops (Storebælt series).\n\nWe will be serving lunch at the meeting
 \, so we kindly ask that you reply to the invitation\, so we know how many
  people to expect. If you have any dietary restrictions/allergies\, please
  let Jeppe know.\n\nLooking forward to seeing you.\n\nBest\,\nMorten & Jep
 pe\n\nJeppe Hartmann\nProject Coordinator\n\nUniversity of Copenhagen\nDep
 artment of Drug Design and Pharmacology\n\nUniversitetsparken 2\nDK - 2100
  Copenhagen\nDenmark\nLync/Skype +45 35323413\njeppe.hartmann@sund.ku.dk<m
 ailto:jeppe.hartmann@sund.ku.dk>\n\n[Logo for Københavns Universitet]\n\n
 How we protect personal data<https://informationssikkerhed.ku.dk/english/p
 rotection-of-information-privacy/privacy-policy/>\n\n\n
